### Description

I use NX monorepo with 17.2.2 Angular version. 
An app has a tailwind.config.js and postcss.config.json file. 

I changed the builder to "application" and made changes in the project.json (known as angular.json) but the compiler shows some warnings (about "content" property not being found) and then errors because it ignores tailwind configuration in the project root. But it works if I put tailwind.config.js in the workspace root.

How can I make the builder find the tailwind configuration in the project root?

The warnings and errors:

![image](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/assets/142388200/2b5fe94d-f77a-4326-924e-9adaba80584d)

